    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-23T17:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-23T17:42:00-05:00" n="665"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/3–2352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d665fn1">This telegram was repeated to London as telegram
                        4688 and for information to New Delhi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-23T17:42:00-05:00"
                            >March 23, 1952—5:42 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>936. 1. Pls take earliest opportunity ascertain from <persName corresp="#p_GDF1"
                        >Graham</persName> latest <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> position re
                    quantum and/or ratio of troops at end demilitarization. On basis available info
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> under impression there may still be
                    room for additional pressure either by US and UK <gloss target="#t_REP1"
                        >Rep</gloss>s in New Delhi or by <persName corresp="#p_GDF1"
                        >Graham</persName> himself in view Indians’ past indications <gloss
                        target="#t_ref1">ref</gloss> to figure of 21,000 not necessarily final.</p>
                <p>2. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> also under impression <persName
                        corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> has not yet discussed concrete proposals
                    re quantum troops, and believes such discussion essential. <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> suggestions to fol.</p>
                <p>3. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> strongly hopes <persName
                        corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> will for present reserve decision re
                    departure for Geneva.</p>
                <pb facs="0154" n="1204" xml:id="pg_1204"/>
                <p>4. Re <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1">Zafrullah</persName>’s inquiry possibility
                    US–UK sponsorship art 37 action you may tell him US position will be governed
                    largely by nature and content <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName>
                    report.</p>
                <p>5. <gloss target="#t_Brit1">Brit</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> Wash alerting London this tel. <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> London pls immed inform <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CRO1">CRO</gloss>
                    who will presumably tele comments and <gloss target="#t_instrs1">instrs</gloss>
                    to <gloss target="#t_UKHC1">UKHC</gloss> Karachi. <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                        >Emb</gloss> Karachi pls consult <gloss target="#t_UKHC1">UKHC</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
